===Adjective===
'''average''' ({{compar}} '''more average''', {{superl}} '''most average''')

# (''not [[comparable]]'') Constituting or relating to the average.
#:''The average age of the participants was 18.5.''
# Neither very good nor very bad; rated somewhere in the middle of all others in the same category.
#:''I soon found I was only an average chess player.''
# Typical.
#:''The average family will not need the more expensive features of this product.''

====Synonyms====
*(''constituting or relating to the average''): [[mean]]
*(''neither very good nor very bad''): [[mediocre]], [[medium]], [[middle]]-[[rank]]ing, [[middling]], [[unremarkable]]
*(''typical''): [[bog-standard]] (''slang''), [[conventional]], [[normal]], [[regular]], [[standard]], [[typical]], [[usual]]

